    <mj-text color="#212b35" font-size="12px" height=15px font-weight="bold">
      Siri Nellutla '23, Staff Writer

    </mj-text>
    <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
      Only 57 women have been awarded a Nobel Prize out of more than 900 recipients.<br>This year’s Nobel Prize in Chemistry was, for the first time, awarded to an exclusively all-female team for their remarkable contributions to the human race. The awardees were Dr. Emmanuelle Charpentier, director of the Max Planck Unit for the Science of Pathogens, and Dr. Jennifer Doudna from the University of California, Berkeley.

